reviews.review: It was a great movie.  lots of action! I personally enjoyed it. my husband said he expected a better fight with ray and kylo.

The movie takes everything that was introduced and everything that was taught to us in the original trilogy and the sequels and throws it in the garbage.  There are too many places and there's so much wasted potential, the force has many new abilities that we get no explanation about and for some resone rey is stronger with the force than anakin (aka the jedi with the highest midichlorian count ever) and has better control over it than yoda with zero training. Rey acts like a sith, she fights with her emotions instead of concentration and acts without thinking, that is how a sith fights, not a jedi, rey will even kill if she has the chance and thats against the nomber 1 rule of the jedi. The last battle was boring and much too short and made no sense. This movie truly was, the worst star wars movie ever created.

Very satisfying ending. Not perfect but powerful and exciting and gorgeously beautiful. So much great stuff in there. Definitely a win for a first viewing. Time will tell how I feel about it in the larger context over time. But lots of stories wrapped up well. And plenty of surprises!
great way to end it! surprises and heart
Well that was a nothing of a movie.
Don’t listen to the critics! Go and have a blast!

From a casual fan perspective, this is a great movie. On paper, the plot points are a bit chishé. They were also pretty predictable, but the rollercoaster of events kept you second guessing. But the overall conclusion of the rollercoaster is generally what I thought it would be. Still though, it is a great conclusion to a great saga

I agree it was a lot to take in for 2 1/2 hours. The ending was strong and as a Mega Fan for the last 41 years, this is right up there with Rogue 1 and Empire Strikes Back. You need to see this one on the big screen. Well done JJ.

A lot better than the previous films in this sequel series, which were absolutely awful and boring. TROS has distinct lack of plot holes, less annoying characters and a more structured story. A shame this had to all be squashed into one film, where this part should have been building, we should have seen the Emperor before this. However, as a standalone film it is enjoyable. What really drags it down is that a) Rey doesn't die, and b) the whole, "I am Rey Skywalker" thing. But I really enjoyed Emperor Palpatine, and the new take on him. Truly disturbing. I also loved the First/Final Order scenes, they were beautiful, dark and sinister. Richard E. Grant was fantastic as Admiral Pryde. 

It really was a tough job, to do a third film and make it stupendous, when you have to retcon and build something from the first two very pointless, plotless films. I hope Star Wars is never again disrespected like it has been through these sequels.

This movie overall was a great movie for any fan of the star wars franchise. It’s truly non stop action with a good sense of humor. It’s always hard to create an ending for a movie franchise the loved, but JJ Abrams did a great job that in a way, many Star Wars fans will enjoy
